{"id":669113,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eco-socialism","text":"e=\"preserve\">Eco-socialism is an ideology that mixes socialism with green politics, environmentalism, ecology, and anti-globalisation. Eco-socialists believe that capitalism (along with imperialism and globalisation) causes war, poverty, and the destruction of the environment.\nEco-socialists want community ownership of the means of production, and to restore the environment.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Ideology","surface_form":"ideology","offset":33},{"uri":"Socialism","surface_form":"socialism","offset":53},{"uri":"Green_politics","surface_form":"green politics","offset":68},{"uri":"Environmentalism","surface_form":"environmentalism","offset":84},{"uri":"Ecology","surface_form":"ecology","offset":102},{"uri":"Antiglobalization","surface_form":"anti-globalisation","offset":115},{"uri":"Capitalism","surface_form":"capitalism","offset":163},{"uri":"Imperialism","surface_form":"imperialism","offset":186},{"uri":"Globalisation","surface_form":"globalisation","offset":202},{"uri":"War","surface_form":"war","offset":224},{"uri":"Poverty","surface_form":"poverty","offset":229},{"uri":"Environment","surface_form":"environment","offset":265},{"uri":"Means_of_production","surface_form":"means of production","offset":325},{"uri":"Environment","surface_form":"environment","offset":365}]}